/*
 * Copyright (c) 2026
 * SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0
 *
 * The "browser bridge" shield: the peripherals a guest gains when the QEMU
 * machine is qemu-wasm running in a browser tab. It is not a physical shield —
 * the devices are provided by patched QEMU models fed by page JavaScript (see
 * tools/qemu-patches/ and tools/qemu-jit-patches/).
 *
 * Everything lives in the per-machine files under boards/: the devices sit at
 * machine-specific addresses (an MMIO gap on the LM3S6965, a spare PL011 slot
 * on virt), so there is nothing meaningful to add for an arbitrary board.
 *
 * boards/qemu_cortex_m3.overlay — GNSS NMEA UART, qemu,host-sensor (with
 *   accel0 / temp0 / light0 / … aliases so stock sensor samples build against
 *   the host sensor), qemu,host-gpio, and qemu,host-audio.
 * boards/qemu_cortex_a53.overlay — GNSS NMEA UART, browser-sized qemu,ramfb,
 *   the same host-sensor node/aliases, and qemu,host-audio.
 */
